  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "Continuity is the internal consistency of a fictional world across its multiple realizations—different works, episodes, installments, tellings, or play sessions set in the same world. A world exhibits continuity when established facts, character histories, spatial relationships, and causal sequences remain coherent from one realization to the next.",
